Learn to create an interactive PDF you can use as the basis for
a great presentation with Adobe InDesign CC. Mike Rankin shows
you how to create a template for your presentation file, and then
how to add your own text and images, play audio and video, and
link to content on the web. Plus, learn how to animate bulleted
lists, create an area for taking notes, and run your presentation
automatically. Last, Mike offers tips for delivering a
presentation that genuinely connects with your audience
